<div class="section sec-cream">
  <div class="container">
    <div style="max-width:820px;margin:0 auto;">
      <span class="section-tag">PAYMENT SCHEDULE</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">Financial Sequencing</h2>
      <div class="divider" style="margin:18px auto 24px"></div>
      <div class="timeline" style="margin:0 auto;max-width:720px;text-align:left">
        <div class="tl-item"><div class="tl-dot"></div><div class="tl-title">Stage 1 — Mobilization Advance: 20%</div><div class="tl-text">Paid on agreement signing to mobilise the site team, secure initial materials, and set up temporary site works.</div></div>
        <div class="tl-item"><div class="tl-dot"></div><div class="tl-title">Stage 2 — Basement Completion: 20%</div><div class="tl-text">Payable after completion of basement slab and associated basement structural works, verified by the site engineer.</div></div>
        <div class="tl-item"><div class="tl-dot"></div><div class="tl-title">Stage 3 — Roof Slab: 20%</div><div class="tl-text">Raised after completion of the topmost floor roof slab and primary waterproofing to protect the structure.</div></div>
        <div class="tl-item"><div class="tl-dot"></div><div class="tl-title">Stage 4 — Brick Work: 10%</div><div class="tl-text">Covers brick work including brick/block laying for walls, bonding, and lintel placement verified by the site engineer.</div></div>
        <div class="tl-item"><div class="tl-dot"></div><div class="tl-title">Stage 5 — Plaster Works: 10%</div><div class="tl-text">Payable on completion of internal and external plaster works, surface preparation for finishes, and curing checks.</div></div>
        <div class="tl-item"><div class="tl-dot"></div><div class="tl-title">Stage 6 — Flooring &amp; Fitouts: 10%</div><div class="tl-text">Covers floor finishes, tiling, electrical & plumbing points, and installation of modular fitouts and fixtures.</div></div>
        <div class="tl-item"><div class="tl-dot"></div><div class="tl-title">Stage 7 — Handover: 5%</div><div class="tl-text">Final payment at handover after snag clearance, painting, and issuance of the Defect Liability Bond and completion certificates.</div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- FAQ -->
<div class="section" style="background:var(--white)">
 <div class="container" style="max-width:800px">
 <span class="section-tag">FAQ</span>
 <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
 <div class="divider"></div>
 <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span>What is the home construction cost per sq ft in Chennai 2026?</span><span class="faq-icon">+</span></div><div class="faq-a"><p>Home construction costs in Chennai in 2026 typically range from ₹1,800 to ₹3,200 per sq. ft. depending on specifications. Morning Star Infra offers 4 packages: Basic (₹1,980), Classic (₹2,430), Premium (₹2,860), and Green Eco (₹2,990) — all fully transparent with no hidden charges.</p></div></div>
 <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span>Do you handle CMDA and DTCP approvals?</span><span class="faq-icon">+</span></div><div class="faq-a"><p>Yes. We provide complete documentation support for CMDA/DTCP approvals. The approval fees are borne by the client, but our team handles all technical drawings, coordination, and submission processes.</p></div></div>
 <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span>What is a Defect Liability Bond and do you provide it?</span><span class="faq-icon">+</span></div><div class="faq-a"><p>A Defect Liability Bond is a legally binding document that commits the contractor to rectify any structural defects within the specified period at no cost to the owner. Morning Star provides a 5-year bond aligned with RERA structural defect standards — issued at handover.</p></div></div>
 <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span>Can Morning Star assist with home loan processing?</span><span class="faq-icon">+</span></div><div class="faq-a"><p>Absolutely. We provide all technical documents required by banks including structural drawings, BOQ, cost estimates, and stage completion certificates needed for home loan disbursement at each construction milestone.</p></div></div>
 <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span>How long does it take to build a standard 2000 sq. ft. house?</span><span class="faq-icon">+</span></div><div class="faq-a"><p>A typical 2000 sq. ft. residential build takes 10–14 months depending on design complexity, number of floors, and approval timelines. We provide a detailed project schedule with milestones before construction begins.</p></div></div>
 </div>
</div>
